        "subject": "LU-3601 Don't enqueue two locks on the same resource",
        "message": "LU-3601 Don't enqueue two locks on the same resource\n\nDue to mechanics of ldlm internals, enqueueing two different ibits\nlock on the same resource is deadlock prone.\nAs such change mdt_object_open_lock to not obtain openlocks at all if\nthe file has no objects (and as such would likely need them created).\n\nChange-Id: Ic3a8e34257264ef6efea8b3a88bb6a2fc0922e5d\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
